:["English: variant of   Cottrell  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cottrell","meanings":["English (southern and western England): status name for a cottager, from Old French <i>coterel</i>, a diminutive of <i>cotier</i> ‘cottager’ (see   Cotter  ). In southwestern England, there may have been some confusion with   Cottle  , the place Frampton <i>Cotterell</i>, earlier recorded as Franton' Ade <i>Cotelli</i>, having been named after the <i>Cotel</i> family, who held the manor from the 12th century."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Cotterell was born in 1350, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with William Washborne. She died in 1396, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1350–1396":"1350–1396","1353–1386":"1353–1386","1373–1410":"1373–1410","1410":"1410","1386":"1386","1353":"1353","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","1350":"1350","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ashford, Devon, England":"Ashford, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1350–1396":"1350–1396","1353–1386":"1353–1386","1373–1410":"1373–1410","1410":"1410","1386":"1386","1353":"1353","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","1350":"1350","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ashford, Devon, England":"Ashford, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1350–1396":"1350–1396","1353–1386":"1353–1386","1373–1410":"1373–1410","1410":"1410","1386":"1386","1353":"1353","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","1350":"1350","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Ashford, Devon, England":"Ashford, Devon, Angleterre","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Cotterell est née en 1350, à Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec William Washborne. Elle est décédée en 1396, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 46 ans."},"de":{"1350–1396":"1350–1396","1353–1386":"1353–1386","1373–1410":"1373–1410","1410":"1410","1386":"1386","1353":"1353","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","1350":"1350","England":"England, United Kingdom","Ashford, Devon, England":"Ashford, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Margaret Cotterell wurde 1350 in Devon, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit William Washborne mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1396 im Alter von 46 Jahren in England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"1350–1396":"1350–1396","1353–1386":"1353–1386","1373–1410":"1373–1410","1410":"1410","1386":"1386","1353":"1353","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","1350":"1350","England":"Angletè, United Kingdom","Ashford, Devon, England":"Ashford, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1350–1396":